\begin{abstract}
\vspace{1.5cm}

Precise biomechanical evaluation in cricket is traditionally restricted to expensive motion-capture environments, leaving amateurs reliant on subjective observation. This project presents a {Posture-Based Detection and Feedback System for Cricket} to democratize elite-level motion analysis using standard 2D video. The system employs a unique Triple-Model AI "Sense-Verify-Advise" architecture to transform raw video into actionable coaching intelligence.

The Perception Layer utilizes Google MediaPipe to extract 33 distinct 3D skeletal landmarks(99 distinct points all together from x,y and z axis) , enabling digital spatial topological mapping and the calculation of kinematic metrics, such as elbow extension, via the Law of Cosines. The Validation Layer utilizes a Random Forest classifier trained on the UCF101 dataset to benchmark amateur kinematics against professional signatures and identify technical deviations like head-dropping or lead-knee collapse. Finally, the Cognitive Layer integrates the OpenAI GPT-4o API to translate biomechanical scalars into human-centric generative coaching heuristics.

Delivered through an asynchronous FastAPI backend with automated PDF auditing via ReportLab, the system eliminates human observation bias and provides accessible, algorithmic technique correction without the need for cost-prohibitive sensor hardware. Cumulative analysis across multiple test cases demonstrates high consistency in detecting biomechanical metrics and successfully identifying diverse stroke categories.
\end{abstract}
