\chapter{Conclusion }
\begin{sloppypar}
    
The development of the Cricket Posture Detection System marks a meaningful step toward blending technology with sports training in a practical and accessible way. What traditionally required the trained eye of an experienced coach can now be assisted by a system that observes, measures, and interprets player movements with consistency and precision. By transforming ordinary video input into detailed biomechanical insights, the project demonstrates how artificial intelligence can move beyond theory and become a useful tool in real-world applications.
\\
\\
Throughout the implementation, the system successfully integrates multiple technologies, including computer vision, machine learning, and web-based frameworks, into a unified workflow. From capturing a user-uploaded video to extracting skeletal landmarks, calculating joint angles, classifying shot types, and finally generating structured feedback, each component contributes to a cohesive analytical process. The use of MediaPipe for pose estimation ensures accurate tracking of body movements, while the machine learning model and rule-based logic provide reliable classification and interpretation of cricket shots.
\\
\\
One of the most impactful aspects of the system lies in its ability to provide understandable and actionable feedback. Rather than simply presenting raw data, the system translates technical analysis into meaningful suggestions, allowing users to identify mistakes and improve their technique. The addition of a downloadable PDF report further enhances usability by offering a permanent record of performance that can be reviewed over time.
\\
\\
At the same time, the project highlights the potential for future enhancements. The current system focuses primarily on elbow angle and basic posture indicators, but it can be extended to include more advanced biomechanical parameters, real-time analysis, and support for multiple sports. Integration with mobile applications or wearable sensors could further improve accuracy and accessibility, making the system even more valuable for athletes and coaches.
\\
\\
In conclusion, this project successfully demonstrates how intelligent systems can assist in sports performance analysis by providing automated, accurate, and user-friendly feedback. It not only reduces dependency on manual observation but also opens the door to more data-driven training methodologies. As technology continues to evolve, systems like this have the potential to become an integral part of modern sports coaching, helping players refine their skills and reach higher levels of performance.
\end{sloppypar}
